From: LotusWorks <apinales@lotusworks.io>
Subject: [PATCH] tlv320adcx140: expand supported rates to 8 kHz–192 kHz

The upstream ADCX140_RATES mask only lists 44.1, 48, 96, and 192 kHz.
Replace it with SNDRV_PCM_RATE_8000_192000 to also support 8, 16, 32,
88.2, and 176.4 kHz, which the codec and RP1 I2S handle cleanly.

384 kHz and 768 kHz are intentionally excluded: the RP1 cannot cleanly
synthesize the required 24.576 MHz BCLK from its 54 MHz crystal without
an external oscillator, producing non-harmonic clock-jitter sidebands
around the signal.

---
 tlv320adcx140.h | 5 +----
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/tlv320adcx140.h
+++ b/tlv320adcx140.h
@@ -5,10 +5,7 @@
 #ifndef _TLV320ADCX140_H
 #define _TLV320ADCX140_H

-#define ADCX140_RATES	(SNDRV_PCM_RATE_44100 | \
-			 SNDRV_PCM_RATE_48000 | \
-			 SNDRV_PCM_RATE_96000 | \
-			 SNDRV_PCM_RATE_192000)
+#define ADCX140_RATES	SNDRV_PCM_RATE_8000_192000

 #define ADCX140_FORMATS	(SNDRV_PCM_FMTBIT_S16_LE | \
 			 SNDRV_PCM_FMTBIT_S20_3LE | \
